{
  "texts": [
    "For the convenience of subsequent analysis, we assign a fixed group of stellar atmospheric parameters to each stellar source using the median of multiple measurements, that is,",
    "where {T i eff }, {log g i }, and {[Fe/H] i } are the sets of the multiple measurements of the three stellar atmospheric parameters, respectively.",
    "The uncertainties of the source parameters (denoted by δT eff, source, δ log g source, and δ[Fe/H] source) are inherited from the uncertainties of the median values.",
    "The peaks of the δT eff, source, δ log g source, and δ[Fe/H] source distributions for the stellar source sample after the above screening conditions are at about 26 K, 0.024 dex, and 0.016 dex, respectively.",
    "For most MRS time-domain objects, the deviations of the stellar parameter values of the multiple measurements from the source values defined in Equation (1) are on the order of magnitude of the parameter uncertainties."
  ]
}